---
title: Seal Skip
hidden: false
---
The&nbsp;**Seal Skip**&nbsp;can be used to skip getting the&nbsp;[Key to the Seal](https://darksouls.wikidot.com/key-to-the-seal)&nbsp;from Ingward and lowering the water in [New Londo Ruins](http://darksouls.wikidot.com/new-londo-ruins) by using a&nbsp;quit-out&nbsp;and&nbsp;[Fall Control](https://darksouls.wikidot.com/fall-control)&nbsp;to get to the [Four Kings](http://darksouls.wikidot.com/the-four-kings).

It was discovered by **Fed981** in December 2014 on PTDE version of the game.

## How to perform this skip ?

There is **two ways** to perform this skip. **The first one** using [Fall-Control Quitout](ds1remaster/fall-damages-cancel#fall-control-quit-out) shown here : [https://youtu.be/RFhuyHVgHKE](https://youtu.be/RFhuyHVgHKE), it is a bit slower compared to the no-fall control method but very safe and easy.

---

**The second one**, a lot more complicated but a bit faster compared to fall control method :

- Medium difficulty & consistent seal skip using [slope roll](/ds1remaster/fall-damages-cancel#slope-rolls) tutorial with bow [https://youtu.be/v-Jl1E6xx1E](https://youtu.be/v-Jl1E6xx1E) by m3dic on YouTube.
- Seal skip demonstration using [slope quitout](/ds1remaster/fall-damages-cancel#slope-quit-out) without bow (1-2sec faster compared to bow method ) [https://youtu.be/X2NwsNKbLY0?t=1196](https://youtu.be/X2NwsNKbLY0?t=1196) by aeiou on YouTube.
